<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 12:22PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Light to occasionally moderate snow will continue for areas
north of I-69, increasing in coverage between now and 2 PM.
* Temperatures at or below 32 F will lead to additional slushy
accumulations on roadways, especially those left untreated.
* Additional accumulations around an inch, although locally
higher amounts remain possible.
IMPACTS...
* Drivers should be prepared for variable road conditions,
especially those left untreated.
* Reductions in visibility to one mile or less at times.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP
MV</description>
